<HL>
   Saint-Gobain Offer for Norton
</HL>
<DATE>
08/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C5
</SO>
<CO>
   F.STG NRT
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
INDUSTRIAL EQUIPMENT, MACHINE TOOLS (IND)
</IN>
<LP>
   PARIS -- French glass and construction materials group
Cie. de Saint-Gobain said it completed its public offer for
Norton Co., with 95% of Norton shares tendered.
   Saint-Gobain said it will pay $90 for each of the 19.5
million shares tendered, bringing the cost of the transaction
to $1.76 billion.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company said it will proceed with the planned merger
of the U.S. unit SG Acquisition Corp. and Norton. The merger
must be approved by a shareholders' meeting, which is
expected to take place the beginning of next month, the
company said.
   Saint-Gobain said shares that weren't tendered will be
eligible for the $90 purchase price after the merger.
</TEXT>
